net.sf.tweety.logics.pl.semantics

Class PriestWorld

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.tweety.commons.AbstractInterpretation
      • net.sf.tweety.logics.pl.semantics.PriestWorld
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    net.sf.tweety.commons.Interpretation

    public class PriestWorld
extends net.sf.tweety.commons.AbstractInterpretation
    A three-valued interpretation for propositional logic from Priest's three valued logic (3VL) [Priest, G.: Logic of paradox. Journal of Philosophical Logic 8, 219-241 (1979)]. Every proposition gets one of three truth values: true, false, both.
    Author:
    Matthias Thimm
